<h3> Exciting Entr&eacute;es </h3>
<h4> <i>Lobia (Black Eyed Peas Curry) </i></h4>
<p>
Coming from an Indian heritage, I love Indian cooking, culture and food! When I moved into
college, I also bought an Instant Pot (<a href = "https://www.amazon.com/Instant-Pot-Multi-Use-Programmable-Pressure/dp/B00FLYWNYQ/ref=sr_1_2?crid=8I5NCIWX6CWB&keywords=instant+pot&qid=1645410597&sprefix=insta%2Caps%2C223&sr=8-2"></a>
 and having it has been a game-changer. I love making tons and tons of dishes using 
 the pressure cooker function. One Indian recipe that I recently made is called 
 lobia, which is Punjabi black eyed peas curry). It can be eatedn with Indian bread
 or rice. 
</p>
<p><b>Ingredients:</b></p>
<ul style="list-style-type:none"> 
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 cup black eyed peas</li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 tablespoon oil</li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 tablespoon cumin seeds</li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 green chili pepper (diced)</li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 cup onion </li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1/2 tablespoon ginger (grated) </li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1/2 tablespoon garlic (minced) </li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 cup tomato </li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 2 cups water </li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 teaspoon lime juice </li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> cilantro (to garnish)</li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1/2 teaspoon ground turmeric</li>  
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1/2-1 teaspoon kashmiri red chili powder</li>
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 teaspoon coriander powder</li>  
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 teaspoon garam masala</li>  
  <li> <input type="checkbox"> 1 teaspoon salt</li> 
</ul>

<p> We start by soaking the black eyed peas in water overnight. I start with the 
instant pot in the saut&eacute; mode. I add the oil and wait until it is heated. 
When hot enough, I add the cumin seeds. Then, we add 
the diced green chili pepper. Once the cumin seeds begin to sputter, I like to add the onions, ginger,
and garlic. After it is well cooked, I add the tomatoes and spices and cook it a little longer. 
Lastly add the black eyed peas (make sure to strain it, first), along with the about
2 cups of water. Then, press "Cancel" to leave the saut&eacute; mode, and begin 
pressure cooking at high pressure for 12 minutes. When done cooking, let the pressure
release manually, stir in lime juice, and garnish with cilantro. 

<br> 
<br>

I like this recipe because it does not take too long and is kind to the wallet, as well!
I also like <a href = "https://pipingpotcurry.com/23-best-instant-pot-indian-recipes/"> Piping Pot Curry </a>, 
which has tons of Indian instant pot recipes!
</p>
